## XFOIL WORKFLOW
1. load up an airfoil -> Load an existing coordinate file or generate one
2. Refine the mesh -> Enter the PPAR or PANE menus to adjust and refine panel nodes along the chord.
3. set the conditions -> Go to the OPER menu, set viscous flow conditions via visc [Reynolds number] and define your angle of attack alfa to compute.
4. plot/export -> Plot the pressure coefficient (\(C_{p}\)) or surface velocity (\(Q\)), and save the calculated aerodynamic data as a polar file.
